OL,3,C600 patients given hospital equipment
OL,4,Cto be treated in their own homes
OL,6,FMs Hodges said: "I returned home from
OL,7,Fhospital to find all the equipment I
OL,8,Fwould need was already waiting for me.
OL,9,FI was also told if my symptoms
OL,10,Fworsened there was no need for me to
OL,11,Fring an ambulance or go to A&E. I
OL,12,Fwould be seen by one of the team right
OL,13,Faway, which is a huge relief for me.
OL,15,F"I much prefer to be cared for in this
OL,16,Fway at home and the team have been so
OL,17,Fattentive, I can't praise them enough."
OL,19,FThe virtual ward team keeps an eye on
OL,20,Fthe readings from their patients from
OL,21,Ftheir office at the hospital.
