OL,3,C600 patients given hospital equipment
OL,4,Cto be treated in their own homes
OL,6,FThe wards can support 25 people at any
OL,7,Fone time - and in 2024 they have cared
OL,8,Ffor over 400 patients.
OL,10,FKate Harwood, a specialist respiratory
OL,11,Fphysiotherapist at WCH said: "The idea
OL,12,Fbehind the virtual wards did come
OL,13,Fafter covid. And the idea is to try
OL,14,Fand free up some hospital beds,
OL,15,Fespecially during the wintertime. It
OL,16,Fdoes really help with winter pressures.
OL,18,F"It's an option for patients, so
OL,19,Fthey're able to be more active in
OL,20,Ftheir shared decision making about
OL,21,Ftheir own hospital care."
